text: Effingham Junction Carriage Holding Sidings is located in Effingham, Surrey, on the New Guildford Line and is near Effingham Junction station. == History == In 1983, Class 416, Class 423 and Class 508 EMUs could be seen. == Present == It is a stabling point for Class 73 locomotives. == References == Category:Railway sidings in England
title: Effingham Junction Carriage Holding Sidings
